# IMPI Scraper Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values

# =============================================================================
# IPFOXY PROXY PROVIDER (Recommended for rotating IPs)
# =============================================================================
# Get your API token from: https://www.ipfoxy.com/
# The scraper can automatically fetch fresh proxy IPs with unique session IDs
# Each session ID gives you a different IP address for concurrent scraping

# Required: Your IPFoxy API token (get from IPFoxy dashboard)
# IPFOXY_API_TOKEN=your_api_token_here

# Optional: IPFoxy gateway settings (defaults shown)
# IPFOXY_HOST=gate-sg.ipfoxy.io
# IPFOXY_PORT=58688

# =============================================================================
# STATIC PROXY CONFIGURATION (Alternative to IPFoxy API)
# =============================================================================

# Option 1: Full proxy URL (includes auth)
# IMPI_PROXY_URL=http://username:password@proxy.example.com:8080

# Option 2: Separate server and credentials
# PROXY_SERVER=http://proxy.example.com:8080
# PROXY_USERNAME=your_username
# PROXY_PASSWORD=your_password

# =============================================================================
# HOW IT WORKS
# =============================================================================
#
# When you set IPFOXY_API_TOKEN, the scraper can call:
#   fetchProxiesFromEnv(count)
#
# This fetches `count` proxy configs, each with a unique session ID.
# Each session ID routes through a different IP address.
#
# Example response for count=3:
#   Proxy 1: customer-xxx-sessid-123_10000 -> IP: 1.2.3.4
#   Proxy 2: customer-xxx-sessid-123_10001 -> IP: 5.6.7.8
#   Proxy 3: customer-xxx-sessid-123_10002 -> IP: 9.10.11.12
#
# This enables concurrent scraping with different IPs to avoid rate limits.
